Key Files
main.c
Description:

main.c is the entry point of the program. It contains the main function, which is the starting point for execution.

numbers.c
Description:

numbers.c contains the implementation of functions related to number sequences and operations.

Importance:

This file includes core functions such as:

naturalNumbers(int n): Prints natural numbers from 1 to n.
reverseNaturalNumbers(int n): Prints reverse natural numbers from n to 1.
evenNumbers(int n): Prints even numbers from 2 to n.
oddNumbers(int n): Prints odd numbers from 1 to n.
sumNaturalNumbers(int n): Calculates the sum of natural numbers from 1 to n.
sumEvenNumbers(int n): Calculates the sum of even numbers from 2 to n.
sumOddNumbers(int n): Calculates the sum of odd numbers from 1 to n.
numbers.h
Description:

numbers.h is a header file that contains function prototypes and definitions used in numbers.c.

Importance:

Provides function declarations for all the functions implemented in numbers.c.
Ensures that main.c and any other files including numbers.h can access and use the functions defined in numbers.c.
